name: Unidentified_Dug_guard

attributes.name: Died
values: During a skirmish in a village

content:
A Dug male guard protected a village, when the village was attacked by bandits who followed Kouru, the guards stepped in to defend the villagers after being signaled by the chief. He was riding a modified probe droid. When the Sith kill their Trandoshan commander, the second wave of bandits killed the other rest of the guards. He also gunned down and crashed into a house.
The Dug first appeared in "The Duel," a short film in the Star Wars: Visions series directed by Takanobu Mizuno, produced by Kamikaze Douga, and released on Disney+ on September 22, 2021. He was voiced by Tasuku Kida in the original Japanese and by Adam Sietz in the English dub.
